{
  "texts": [
    "(54) using N pairs of simulated light curves, and cast it in a Bayesian framework to obtain:",
    "where d is now difference light curve data, i.e.",
    "a set of measurements Δm obs,t and their associated uncertainties, σ t for one or more pairs of multiple images.",
    "The velocity model presented in Sect. 3.4.1 can serve as the prior for η v here.",
    "The posterior probabilities for any parameter of the model can be obtained by marginalizing over all the other remaining free parameters."
  ]
}